HBO's Bill Maher calls on the news media to calm down and give a proper perspective to their coverage of COVID-19.
"Now that we’re starting to see some hope in all this, don’t hope-shame me," the "Real Time" host said.
But at some point, the daily drumbeat of depression and terror veers into panic porn," he added.
"Giving the proper perspective isn’t a cover-up of the truth.
It is the truth... We need the news to calm down and treat us like adults... Trump calls you fake news.